Implementation summary:
- Both helpers live in namespace VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Tests.TestSupport
  inside the existing VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Tests.Runtime asmdef. No new
  asmdef was required: tasks.md §1.5 only asks for the helpers to be placed
  in Tests/Runtime/TestSupport/ and reachable from other tests, which is
  satisfied because every test asmdef already references either the Runtime
  test asmdef indirectly (through Abstractions) or shares it directly.
- TestMainThreadPump intentionally does not depend on UnityEngine or
  PlayerLoop. It is a pure C# pump that invokes registered Flush actions on
  demand. The eventual MainThreadDispatchQueue (task 2.2) can register its
  Flush method and tests can drive it with Pump() instead of running the
  PlayerLoop.
- FakeClock is internally driven by a list-based scheduler keyed on
  DateTimeOffset. Advance fires the earliest due callback first, updates
  UtcNow to that callback's due time, then loops; this means callbacks
  observe the same UtcNow they were scheduled relative to. Final UtcNow is
  the Advance target. The eventual RequestCorrelationRegistry (task 2.3) and
  ReconnectBackoff (task 3.2) can use it to decouple from System.Threading.
  Timer in tests.
- The Tests/Runtime asmdef previously contained zero test files, so the
  PlayMode runner reported "no tests" historically. Adding
  RuntimeAssemblySmokeTests + the TestSupport tests makes the PlayMode tab
  green from this task forward, satisfying the observable completion
  condition "Test Runner で Runtime / Editor 両カテゴリの空テストが緑になり".

